Description:

General Contracting company is looking for a Superintendent with  experience with public construction projects with NYC SCA/ 

Responsibilities:
•	Immediately developing a detailed understanding of all project drawings, specifications, general conditions, and contracts;
•	Active supervision of direct labor and jobsite including troubleshooting solutions to construction means and methods issues that arise; 
•	Scheduling and managing field and project meetings; 
•	Coordinating with and maintaining positive relationships with project architects, engineers, and customers;
•	Managing subcontractors to make sure they perform as required within schedule; 
•	Understanding scopes of work and timely managing deviations per contract provisions;


Established Brooklyn based office seeks Architect with experience to work with Principal to conceptualize, develop, and advance design for a multitude of projects including new construction and renovations for New York residential and commercial projects.

Requirements:
- Must have an Architectural Degree
- Must be a NYS Registered Architect License
- Must have a minimum of 4-10 years of work experience in New York City;
- Must have have an in-depth understanding of NYC Dept. of Buildings Code and Zoning;
- At ease with product research, design, drawing, development of architectural plans, elevations & specs;
- Possess time management and organizational skills;
- Knowledge of mechanical, electrical and plumbing systems;
- Complete basic sketches to clarify field conditions and designs change;
- Proficient in Revit, AutoCAD, PhotoCAD, Photoshop, Microsoft Office and Adobe
- Must be a team player.

Salary based on experience.

For consideration of this position, notate "ARCHITECT" in the subject line of e-mail, attach a copy of recent resume along with sample(s) of your best work in PDF format/links for online viewing.

This is not a sponsored position.

Principals only please.


Tectonic is a multi-disciplined engineering firm that has been in business for over 30 years, and has a reputation for delivering professional, quality services without sacrificing integrity or value. We are also one of only a few uniquely positioned consulting engineering firms that can provide our clients with a higher level of quality services by offering special inspections and in-house laboratory material testing services.

Tectonic is currently seeking qualified Professional Engineers to perform various special inspections on behalf of one of the New York City metro area’s highly respected engineering/inspection firms.  The ideal candidate will have a BSCE and a NYS PE license or the ability to obtain in a short period of time, and geotechnical or building construction experience.    

ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS

Essential functions of this position includes performing various special inspections of building for which the design requires professional engineers to ensure compliance with approved construction documented and referenced standards required by the NYC Construction Building Code. The Senior Field Engineer will also perform additional special testing, including the subsurface investigation including soil borings, test pits, and soil percolation testing. This requires readings and interpreting various related documents and drawings, maintaining special inspection records, and preparing official field reports. The Senior Field Engineer may also perform various other inspections, as well as all other related duties as required. 

QUALIFICATIONS

•	Valid Professional Engineering License required;
•	BS Degree or equivalent in Civil Engineering or similar; MS Degree is a plus;
•	Must possess a minimum of 3 years of geotechnical engineering or construction building inspection experience, preferably in NYC;
•	Ability to complete OSHA 10-Hour Construction Safety and Health Training within a reasonable time period;
•	Ability to prepare and submit timely and accurate field inspection reports;
•	Excellent oral and written communication skills; 
•	Understanding of the fundamentals of building inspection codes and requirements in order to carry out testing, including, but not limited to, International Building Codes, ASTM Standards, and TMS standards; 
•	Diversified knowledge of technology, materials, equipment, design concepts and construction techniques;
•	Ability to solve complex issues with limited direction;
•	May also require valid, clean driver’s license and personal vehicle to travel to job sites.

